[31m-# HOWTO â€” Tools Overlay Content & CTA Wiring[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This guide explains how to update the modal overlays that back the Tools section on `index.html`.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 1. Update overlay copy[m
[31m-[m
[31m-* Source file: [`js/tools-overlay.js`](../js/tools-overlay.js)[m
[31m-* Content lives in the `overlayCopy` map (keys: `signal-forge`, `specterscan`).[m
[31m-* Each entry contains a `title` string and a `body` HTML template string.[m
[31m-* Keep markup simple (headings, paragraphs, lists) and ensure all text is **English**.[m
[31m-* After edits, run `node tools/audit-sitemap.js` to verify language compliance if the copy changed significantly.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 2. Wire CTA buttons to overlays[m
[31m-[m
[31m-* CTA markup lives inside `index.html` under the `#tools` section.[m
[31m-* Each button must include:[m
[31m-  * `class="btn btn-cta"`[m
[31m-  * `type="button"`[m
[31m-  * `data-overlay="<key>"` where `<key>` matches an entry in `overlayCopy`[m
[31m-  * A descriptive `aria-label` (e.g., "Learn more about Signal Forge").[m
[31m-* Re-using the existing `btn-cta` class ensures the pulsing animation and focus ring stay consistent.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 3. Accessibility & motion notes[m
[31m-[m
[31m-* The overlay container (`#tools-overlay`) uses `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, and references `tools-overlay-title`/`tools-overlay-body`.[m
[31m-* Focus is trapped inside the dialog; `Esc`, the close button, and backdrop clicks all dismiss the overlay and restore focus to the trigger button.[m
[31m-* Body scroll locks while the overlay is open via `body.is-overlay-open`.[m
[31m-* `prefers-reduced-motion` disables the CTA pulse animation and removes overlay fade transitions, so avoid introducing large motion in custom content.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 4. Adding more overlays[m
[31m-[m
[31m-* Extend the `overlayCopy` map with a new key/value pair.[m
[31m-* Add a matching CTA button (`data-overlay="new-key"`).[m
[31m-* Optional: adjust styles in `styles.css` under the `.overlay` block if the new content requires different sizing.[m
